Here's how to implement all three requirements:

## 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button (in your page XAML)

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                           Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- page content -->
</ContentPage>
```

## 2. ViewModel with Back Command

```csharp
public partial class EditProductViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task Back()
    {
        if (HasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            bool discard = await Shell.Current.CurrentPage
                .DisplayAlert("Unsaved Changes",
                    "Discard changes?", "Discard", "Stay");
            if (!discard) return;
        }
        await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
    }
}
```

## 3. Guard the Hardware/Gesture Back (in AppShell.xaml.cs)

The custom button handles tap, but you also need to intercept the system back gesture:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.BindingContext is EditProductViewModel vm
        && vm.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await page.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes", "Discard changes?", "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `GetDeferral()` is required for async checks in `OnNavigating` â€” without it the navigation completes before your dialog returns.
- `BackButtonBehavior.Command` handles the toolbar button tap; `OnNavigating` catches swipe-back and hardware back.
- Always `await` `GoToAsync`.
